<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 09 at 9:52AM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Periods of snow across Southwest Montana...
At 9:30am, a band of moderate snow extended across southern
Beaverhead, Madison, and Gallatin counties. The band of snow is
moving to the north, and could reach as far as Dillon to Norris
to Bozeman by early afternoon. Expect new snow accumulations of 1
to 3 inches under this band of snow. Highway cameras show that
snow and ice has accumulated on road surfaces. Improvement is
expected as the road surface warms, but impacts to travel may
continue with reduced visibility. Plan for variable driving
conditions through this afternoon.</description>
